<br>
masamune shirow (its all in the girls...roar!)<br>
my best art bud flux (the basics man)<br>
dark Locke (still amazes me)<br>
Naska (cuteness factor off scale)<br>
<br>
and various others. if ya need help on finding artists to pick styles you like or change to make your own, just shout.<br>
<br>
oh yes and practice. FOR THE LOVE OF GOD PRACTICE!<br>
<br>
-puko <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://128.200.136.11/jason/"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://128.200.136.11/jason/advertkupo.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrcrowleyx>mr crowleyx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/03 2:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12566.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: skill improovmant techniques.....</span><hr size=1> your art teacher bangs on about it all day but DRAW FROM LIFE!!!!!! as often as possible, this makes you fluent at drawing all things then a style will naturally evolve.<br>
<br>
set yourself little tasks, 30 second drawings, use wrong hand, use only brushes, put a drawing tool on the end of a long stick (theory being if you can control at range imagine what you can do at a normal distancce from the paper)<br>
practice, experiment. enjoy!<br>
<br>
the most important thing though is to observe, develop an eye for detail. spend more time looking then drawing. then translate to the page. these exercised help you memorise how things look move and work so you can recall this info when you need it.<br>
remember:<br>
drawing is like a muscle, you gotta train it regular to keep it strong. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrcrowleyx>mr crowleyx</A> at: 7/22/03 4:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=linabo>LinaBo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>PK Angel</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12566.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.silenttransit.com/linavatar.jpg width=113 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: skill improovmant techniques.....</span><hr size=1> a safer bet (not to say that Kupo is wrong. different things work for different people) is to mimic 'life'. work with photos. natural poses etc. street scenes, things like that where people aren't focusing on being unnatural in front of the camera. you can always develop style from reality, but you cannot develop reality from style. <p>'I'll try being nicer if you try being smarter'</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kupozero>kupo zero</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thaaron.com/moogle/images/icons/Mog_f.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/03 4:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12566.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://128.200.136.11/jason/newicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: skill improovmant techniques.....</span><hr size=1> hehe yeah forgot about the life art stuff teehe