<br>
So when you're looking at a face to draw, don't see it as a face, see it as a collection of lines and tones. Also avoid naming things while you draw them (&quot;ok, now I'll draw the eye&quot;) because as the human brain develops we (apparently) create symbols for objects we see every day (like eyes) so the brain wants to plunk that symbol down on the paper instead of what's really there. <br>
<br>
Look at the negative space around an object (this helps when you're drawing from your imagination too...) because what isn't there is just as important as what is. Or something like that.<br>
<br>
...and that's pretty much all I can think of right now... <p>&quot;It's a small, off-duty Czechoslovakian traffic warden!&quot;<br>
   -Kryten<br>
